  "local_port": 56518,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How a B.Tech CSE can get a job at ISRO?",
  "response": "Getting a job at the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) as a B.Tech Computer Science (CSE) graduate can be a rewarding career path, given the organization's prestigious role in space research and development. Here are some steps and tips to guide you through the process:\n\n1. **Educational Qualifications:**\n   - Ensure that you have a strong academic record in your B.Tech CSE degree. ISRO typically requires candidates to have a minimum aggregate percentage, often around 65% or higher.\n\n2. **Understand the Roles:**\n   - ISRO hires CSE graduates for various roles such as Scientist/Engineer in Computer Science, Software Engineer, Data Analyst, etc. Familiarize yourself with these roles and their requirements.\n\n3. **Entrance Exams:**\n   - The most common entry point for engineers into ISRO is through the ISRO Centralized Recruitment Board (ICRB) exam. Keep an eye on their notifications, usually published on ISRO\u2019s official website.\n   - The exam typically covers technical subjects relevant to your field, quantitative aptitude, reasoning, and general knowledge.\n\n4. **Research and Preparation:**\n   - Study the exam pattern and syllabus thoroughly. Previous years' question papers can provide insights into the types of questions asked.\n   - Strong preparation in core computer science subjects like Data Structures, Algorithms, Operating Systems, Computer Networks, Databases, etc., is crucial.\n\n5. **Develop Skills and Experience:**\n   - Proficiency in programming languages (such as C, C++, Python, Java) and software development is vital.\n   - Internships, projects, or work experience in related fields can strengthen your application.\n\n6. **Application Process:**\n   - Once the recruitment notification is out, submit your application through ISRO\u2019s official career portal. Ensure that you meet all eligibility criteria and that your application is complete.\n\n7. **Interview Preparation:**\n   - If you pass the written exam, you\u2019ll be invited for an interview. This usually involves technical questions about your subject, practical problem-solving, and possibly questions about current affairs in space research.\n   - Brush up on your projects and internships as you may be asked about those.\n\n8. **Stay Updated:**\n   - Keep abreast of the latest advancements in computer science and technology, as well as ISRO's missions and projects.\n\n9. **Higher Studies:**\n   - Consider pursuing higher education (such as an M.Tech or a Ph.D.) in a specialized area of interest relevant to ISRO\u2019s projects, which might enhance your prospects.\n\n10. **Networking:**\n    - Engage with professional networks, attend conferences, and participate in workshops related to space research and computer science.\n\nBy following these steps, you can increase your chances of securing a fulfilling position at ISRO. Each step requires dedication and consistent effort, so keep persevering and improving your skills. Good luck!",
